description: BusyBox v1.7.2 (2017-01-10 11:53:04 CST) is a multi-functional Unix toolset that includes streamlined implementations of many common Unix utilities. This version contains multiple known vulnerabilities, including command injection and privilege escalation flaws.

GNU Wget 1.12 is a network download utility with two known vulnerabilities: CVE-2009-3490 (X.509 certificate handling vulnerability) and CVE-2010-2252 (filename processing vulnerability), which may permit man-in-the-middle attacks or arbitrary file writing.
utelnetd is a lightweight telnet server, with no clear version information available. Further analysis is required to determine if any known vulnerabilities exist.
eapd is an authentication protocol daemon, and no clear version information has been found. Further analysis is required to determine whether any known vulnerabilities exist.
Ookla is a network performance testing tool, and no clear version information has been found. Further analysis is required to determine if any known vulnerabilities exist.
wps_monitor is a Wi-Fi Protected Setup monitoring tool, with no clear version information identified. Further analysis is required to determine if any known vulnerabilities exist.
